   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
      <p>
Comments
</p>
      <p>
The 
<tp:taxon-name>Aphalarinae</tp:taxon-name>
is strongly supported as a monophylum in molecular analyses (

Percy 
et al
. 2018

; 

Cho 
et al
. 2019

), morphologically (
Loginova 1964
; 
Brown &amp; Hodkinson 1988
; 
Burckhardt &amp; Queiroz 2013
; 

Ouvrard 
et al
. 2013

) and by the pattern of sperm formation (

Labina 
et al
. 2014

). The subfamily includes two monophyletic tribes: the extant 
<tp:taxon-name>Aphalarini</tp:taxon-name>
and the extinct 
<tp:taxon-name>Paleopsylloidini</tp:taxon-name>
†.
</p>
